Extracting Questions and answers from any webpage's faq section using pytorch
使用 pytorch 從任何網頁的常見問題解答部分提取問題和答案

I want to extract questions and answers from any webpage's FAQ section.
我想從任何網頁的常見問題部分提取問題和答案。

An example: https://aws.amazon.com/ec2/autoscaling/faqs/ https://one.google.com/faq
範例：https://aws.amazon.com/ec2/autoscaling/faqs/ https://one.google.com/faq

Currently I do this using regex parsing of html content of the page but thats very fragile, and only work 60% of the time. This is because website dont follow any standerd approach while writing their markup. So its hard to write a regex based solution that works for all of them.
目前，我使用正規表示式解析頁面的 html 內容來執行此操作，但這非常脆弱，並且只能在 60% 的時間內工作。這是因為網站在編寫標記時不遵循任何標準方法。因此，很難編寫一個適用於所有這些問題的基於正規表示式的解決方案。

I want to know if its possible to do this via ML.
我想知道是否可以透過機器學習來做到這一點。

To be honest I think what you are asking is not that simple.
說實話，我覺得你問的問題沒那麼簡單。

You could definetly try to train an algorithm to identify specific Q&A parts of websites, and extract them. This however would involve using relevant data to train the algorithm, which can be hard to find.
您絕對可以嘗試訓練一種演算法來識別網站的特定問答部分，並將其提取出來。然而，這將涉及使用相關數據來訓練演算法，而這些數據可能很難找到。

Searching for research on this topic in Google Scholar for example, is always a good idea.
例如，在 Google Scholar 中搜尋有關該主題的研究始終是一個好主意。

As an example see here.
作為範例，請參見此處。

That being said, if I were to approach this issue, I would follow a different path:
話雖這麼說，如果我要解決這個問題，我會採取不同的路徑：

  1. Extract all the text from a webpage
    從網頁中提取所有文本
  2. Try to analyze the text to see whether it is Q&A text
    試著分析文本，看看是否為問答文本

This approach might not be optimal but feels easier because there are numerous resources (NLTK, spaCy, scikit-learn) for analyzing and manupulating text.
這種方法可能不是最佳的，但感覺更容易，因為有大量的資源（ NLTK 、 spaCy 、 scikit-learn ）用於分析和操作文本。

  • Using one of these resources you could apply heuristic rules to determine if the text is Q&A (category).
    使用這些資源之一，您可以應用啟發式規則來確定文字是否為問答（類別）。
  • Alternatively you could treat this problem as a classification task and train a supervised algorithm (e.g. Naive Bayes, SVM, kNN, among others) to determine if a piece of text is Q&A or not.
    或者，您可以將此問題視為分類任務並訓練監督演算法（例如 Naive Bayes 、 SVM 、 kNN 等）來確定文字是否為問答。

Feel free to add information in your question or comment, in case I can provide a more detailed answer.
請隨意在您的問題或評論中添加信息，以便我可以提供更詳細的答案。

If you really want to try extracting questions and answers from webpages using ML models, your best bet would be to use one of those huge pre-trained language models out there, like OpenAI GPT3.
如果您確實想嘗試使用 ML 模型從網頁中提取問題和答案，那麼最好的選擇是使用那些巨大的預訓練語言模型之一，例如 OpenAI GPT3。

The following code is an example on how you could try to use GPT3 to try to extract QAs from a general website:
以下程式碼是如何嘗試使用 GPT3 從一般網站提取 QA 的範例：

Note: you need an API Key to be able to run this solution.
注意：您需要 API 金鑰才能執行此解決方案。

"""
Define the `CodexQAExtractor` class, that extracts questions and answers from
website pages.

.. attention::

   To use this code you need to have an OpenAI account and an API key.
   In addition, you need to install the `openai` package:

    .. code-block:: bash

         $ pip install openai

How to use
----------
The following code exemplifies how you can use this code to extract questions
and answers from website pages:

.. code-block:: python

    extractor = CodexQAExtractor(openai_api_key=OPENAI_API_KEY)
    response = extractor.extract_qa_from_url(url_link)

"""
from __future__ import annotations

import os.path
from pathlib import Path
import numpy as np
import requests
import openai


if OPENAI_API_KEY := os.getenv("OPENAI_API_KEY"):
    openai.api_key = OPENAI_API_KEY


def read_from_url(url_text: str) -> str | None:
    """Read text from a URL.

    Parameters
    ----------
    url_text : str
        URL to read from.

    Returns
    -------
    str | None
        Text read from the URL, if `url_text` is a valid URL.
    """
    try:
        file = requests.get(url_text)
        return file.text
    except Exception as exc:
        print(exc)
        print(
            f'Failed to read url: "{url_text}". '
            "See the above exception message for more details."
        )


def extract_text_from_html(html_text: str) -> str | None:
    """Extract text from HTML.

    Parameters
    ----------
    html_text : str
        HTML to extract text from.

    Returns
    -------
    str | None
        Text extracted from the HTML, if `html_text` is valid HTML.
    """
    contents = html_text.split("<body")[1].split(">", 1)[1].split("</body")[0]
    parsed = []
    for text in contents.split(">"):
        if "</" in text:
            new_text = text.split("</")[0].replace("\n", "").replace("\t", "")
            while "  " in new_text:
                new_text = new_text.replace("  ", " ")
            while len(new_text) > 0 and new_text[0] == " ":
                new_text = new_text[1:]
            if len(new_text) > 5:
                parsed.append(new_text)
    return ";".join(parsed)


def is_authenticated() -> bool:
    """Check if the user is authenticated with OpenAI.

    Returns
    -------
    bool
        `True` if the user is authenticated with OpenAI.
    """
    return len(openai.api_key) > 0


def is_float_norm(*args) -> bool:
    """Check if the arguments are floats between 0 and 1.

    Parameters
    ----------
    args : float
        Arguments to check.

    Returns
    -------
    bool
        `True` if the arguments are numbers between 0 and 1.

    Notes
    -----
    Function used for verifying the parameters that the user specified to
    the `CodexQAExtractor.extract_qa` method.
    """
    return not any(
        not isinstance(arg, float) or not 0 <= arg <= 1 for arg in args
    )


class CodexQAExtractor:
    """
    Class to extract questions and answers from a text derived from website.

    Parameters
    ----------
    response_dir : str, default "./answers"
        Directory to save the responses.
    openai_api_key : str | None, default None
        OpenAI API key to use. If `None`, class assumes that the API key is
        already set.

    Attributes
    ----------
    response_dir : str
        Directory to save the responses.

    Methods
    -------
    get_response_filename()
        Get the filename to save the response to.
    extract_qa_from_url(url_text: str, **kwargs) -> str | None
        Extract questions and answers from a URL.
    extract_qa(text: str, **kwargs) -> str | None
        Extract questions and answers from a text.
    """

    def __init__(
        self, response_dir: str = "./answers", openai_api_key: str | None = None
    ):
        if openai_api_key is not None:
            openai.api_key = openai_api_key
        Path(response_dir).mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
        self.response_dir = response_dir

    def get_response_filename(self) -> str:
        """Get the filename to save the response to."""
        next_index = int(len(list(Path(self.response_dir).glob("*.txt"))) + 1)
        return f"{self.response_dir}{os.path.sep}answer_{next_index}.txt"

    def extract_qa(
        self,
        parsed_text: str,
        temperature: float = 0.0,
        top_p: float = 1.0,
        frequency_penalty: float = 0.0,
        presence_penalty: float = 0.0,
        best_of: int = 1,
        max_tokens: int | None = None,
        verbose: bool = True,
        **kwargs,  # noqa
    ) -> str:
        """Extract questions and answers from a text.

        Parameters
        ----------
        parsed_text : str
            Text to extract questions and answers from.
        temperature : float, default 0.0
            Temperature for the probability distribution used to sample
            different tokens at each step. Must be between 0 and 1.
        top_p : float, default 1.0
            The cumulative probability for top-p sampling. Must be between 0
            and 1.
        frequency_penalty : float, default 0.0
            The probability of a token being penalized if it appears too
            frequently in the current sequence. Must be between 0 and 1.
        presence_penalty : float, default 0.0
            The probability of a token being penalized if it appears in the
            current sequence. Must be between 0 and 1.
        best_of : int, default 1
            Number of responses to generate and return.
        max_tokens : int | None, default None
            Maximum number of tokens to generate. If `None`, the number of
            tokens is set by the method.
        verbose : bool, default True
            Whether to print the response to the console.

        Returns
        -------
        str
            Extracted questions and answers from `parsed_text`.

        Raises
        ------
        ValueError
            - If `temperature`, `top_p`, `frequency_penalty`, `presence_penalty`
            are not between 0 and 1.
            - If `best_of` is not a positive integer between 1 and 20.
            - If `max_tokens` is not a positive integer between 1 and 8000.
            - If prompt contains more than 8000 tokens.

        Notes
        -----
        Method assumes that `parsed_text` contains text that was already
        preprocessed, and is not pure HTML string. You can use the function
        `extract_text_from_html` to extract text from HTML:

            .. code-block:: python

                parsed_text = extract_text_from_html(html_text)

        """
        if not is_authenticated():
            raise ValueError(
                "OpenAI API key is not set. Inform a valid token using the "
                "parameter `openai_api_key` from `CodexQAExtractor` class, or "
                "set it as follows:\n\n\timport openai\n\topenai.api_key = "
                '"YOUR_API_KEY"\n'
            )

        if not is_float_norm(
            temperature, top_p, frequency_penalty, presence_penalty
        ):
            raise ValueError(
                "Parameters `temperature`, `top_p`, `frequency_penalty`, "
                "`presence_penalty` must be between 0 and 1. Got\n"
                f"- temperature: {temperature}\n"
                f"- top_p: {top_p}\n"
                f"- frequency_penalty: {frequency_penalty}\n"
                f"- presence_penalty: {presence_penalty}\n"
            )
        if not isinstance(best_of, int) or not 1 <= best_of <= 20:
            raise ValueError(
                "Parameter `best_of` must be an integer between 1 and 20. "
                f"Got: {best_of} of type {type(best_of)}."
            )
        prompt = (
            '# Extract questions and answers from the following text:\n"""\n'
            f'{parsed_text}"""\n###\n"""\nQ:'
        )
        # Prompt exceeds the maximum number of tokens that you can use for a single prompt.
        if len(prompt) > 32000:
            lowbound = 0
            final_response = ""
            # Breaking `parsed_text` smaller parts and extracting QA's from
            # each sepparatelly. This most likely will make the result
            # a lot worse...
            # Note: you could try overcome this by including some of
            #       the text from the previous iteration into the new one.
            for upbound in np.arange(5000, len(parsed_text)+1, 5000):
                final_response += self.extract_qa(
                    parsed_text[lowbound: upbound],
                    temperature,
                    top_p,
                    frequency_penalty,
                    presence_penalty,
                    best_of,
                    max_tokens,
                    verbose,
                )
                lowbound = upbound
            return final_response
                    
        if max_tokens is None:
            max_tokens = int((8_000 - len(prompt) / 4) * 0.65)
        if not isinstance(max_tokens, int) or not 1 <= max_tokens <= 8_000:
            raise ValueError(
                "Parameter `max_tokens` must be an integer between 1 and 8000. "
                f"Got: {max_tokens} of type {type(max_tokens)}."
            )
        response = openai.Completion.create(
            model="code-davinci-002",
            prompt=prompt,
            temperature=temperature,
            max_tokens=max_tokens,
            top_p=top_p,
            frequency_penalty=frequency_penalty,
            presence_penalty=presence_penalty,
            best_of=best_of,
            stop=['"""', "###"],
        )["choices"][0]["text"]

        response = f"Q:{response}"

        with open(self.get_response_filename(), "w", encoding="utf-8") as file:
            file.write(response)
        if verbose:
            print(response)
        return response

    def extract_qa_from_url(self, url_text: str, **kwargs) -> str | None:
        """Extract questions and answers from the given URL.

        Method retrieves the HTML element from the `url_text`, then extracts
        relevant text from the HTML code before calling
        `CodexQAExtractor.extract_qa` to extract the questions and answers
        from the HTML code.

        Parameters
        ----------
        url_text : str
            URL to extract questions and answers from.
        kwargs : Any
            Additional arguments to pass to the `CodexQAExtractor.extract_qa`
            method.

        Returns
        -------
        str
            The extracted questions and answers from the URL.
        """
        html_text = read_from_url(url_text)
        if html_text is None:
            print("Failed to download the HTML elements from the URL, or"
                  "parse its text.")
            return
        page_contents = extract_text_from_html(html_text)
        return self.extract_qa(page_contents, **kwargs)

Extracting questions and answers from the website that you gave as example:
從您給出的範例網站中提取問題和答案：

qa_model = CodexQAExtractor()
test_url = "https://aws.amazon.com/ec2/autoscaling/faqs/?nc1=h_ls"
res = qa_model.extract_qa_from_url(test_url)
